Ecuador Budget to Rise 8.6 Percent in 2012, Ministry Says

-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 
2011-09-28T23:06:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/ecuador-budget-to-rise-8-6-percent-in-2012-ministry-says.html
Ecuador ’s budget will increase by
8.6 percent next year to about $26 billion, Victor Carvajal, a
spokesman for the South America nation’s Finance Ministry said.  Ecuador, South America’s seventh-biggest economy, hasn’t
said how much it needs to finance public spending or provided
growth estimates, Carvajal said today in a telephone interview
from Quito.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in Quito at 
